reviewText: This course is laughable. The presenter is reading everything with a choppy gate and because her notes are on a screen above her is distractingly never exactly looking into the camera. The information is completely common sense on one hand, or completely Amazon specific on the other. I would not recommend this to anyone unless you wanted to upset them.

An excellent course for those whishing to learn and acquire the knowledge as well as skillsets for leadership in engineering roles (e.g. lead, manager, director etc.)

Nancy's professional background and work experiences in major tech corporations provided valuable insights into how leadership is nurtured in those companies.  In addition, she skillfully presented these insights into digestible units over several modules.

Looking forward to more courses from AWIT.

Thank you and best regards!

The concepts in this course are presented very clearly and explained in a way that they can be applied in the real world.  The course is aimed at those wanting to move into an engineering leadership role or those wanting to improve on the basics of that role and I think the material is both relevant and well-calibrated for those audiences.
I enjoyed listening through this course while going about my day. Nancy should start a podcast she's very insightful.
This content seemed more relevant than what I learned elsewhere about how to manage.
great to see a female engineering leader giving back
I didn't know what managers actually did until taking this course.
